Quote: (New N.Z. Process Replaces `Pie' Wool) This machine, known as the Slipemaster, is now in operation in the majority of New Zealand freezing works, and New Zealand-made machines have been sold to Australia and England.
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1976
Source: Pallet on the Floor
Author: MORRIESON
Vol / Page: 94
Edition:
Quote: He had expected to find Entwistle standing at the bend of one of the slipe masters, the machines which had replaced the outcast but fabulously paid gang of men whose job had been to save the precious strands of wool after maggots had devoured the adhering meat. ... He was obliged to watch the steam-gauge of his slipe-master, put up with the roar of the machinery, and sort out and grade the wool which fell on his bench. This wool was thrown into baskets.
